greatCircleIntermediat       package:geosphere       R Documentation

_I_n_t_e_r_m_e_d_i_a_t_e _p_o_i_n_t_s _o_n _a _g_r_e_a_t _c_i_r_c_l_e

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Get intermediate points on a great circle inbetween the two points
     used to define the circle

_U_s_a_g_e:

     greatCircleIntermediate(p1, p2, n=50) 

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

      p1: Longitude/latitude of a single point; can be a vector of two
          numbers, a matrix of 2 columns (first one is longitude,
          second is latitude) or a spatialPoints* object

      p2: As above

       n: The requested number of points on the Great Circle

_V_a_l_u_e:

     a matrix of points

_A_u_t_h_o_r(_s):

     Robert Hijmans based on code by Ed Williams

_R_e_f_e_r_e_n_c_e_s:

     <URL: http://williams.best.vwh.net/avform.htm#Intermediate>

_E_x_a_m_p_l_e_s:

     greatCircleIntermediate(c(5,52), c(-120,37), n=10)

